# Privacy Policy for Flaunt

**Effective date:** June 6, 2026

Flaunt is a local-only notes and recording app for songwriters. This policy explains, plainly, what happens to your information when you use it.

**The short version:** Flaunt does not collect, transmit, sell, or share any of your data. Everything you create stays on your device, in a folder you choose. There are no accounts, no servers, no analytics, and no ads.

---

## What Flaunt stores

Flaunt saves the content you create — your lyrics and notes (as plain Markdown files), your audio recordings, and the metadata that organizes them (titles, song/album groupings, renditions, BPM, key, and similar). It also saves your app preferences, such as your chosen theme and default font.

All of this is stored **locally on your device**, inside a storage folder that you select (or a default location on your device if you don't choose one). Flaunt does not upload this content anywhere. We — the developer — never see it and have no access to it.

## What Flaunt does *not* do

- It does **not** require an account or sign-in.
- It does **not** collect personal information.
- It does **not** use analytics, tracking, advertising, or third-party data-collection SDKs.
- It does **not** transmit your notes, recordings, or metadata over the internet.

## Permissions

- **Microphone** — used only to record audio takes within the app, when you start a recording. Recordings are written directly to your local storage folder and are never sent anywhere.
- **Storage / file access** — used so Flaunt can save and read your notes and audio in the folder you choose. On Android this is granted through the system folder picker; Flaunt only accesses the location you point it to.

## Backups and exports

Any backup or export you create (for example, exporting a song or an album as a `.zip`, or backing up your library) is written to the location **you** choose at that moment, using your device's standard file picker. These files contain your own content and are handled entirely by you. Flaunt does not send them anywhere.

On Android, Flaunt also disables the operating system's automatic cloud backup of its internal app data, so your in-app data is not copied to a cloud service by the OS.

## Links to other apps and websites

Flaunt can open links you add to a note (for example, a reference URL) in your device's browser or another app. Once you leave Flaunt, the privacy practices of that browser, app, or website apply — not this policy.

## Children's privacy

Flaunt does not collect any data from anyone, including children, and is not directed at children under 13. Because no information is collected or transmitted, there is nothing for us to gather about any user.

## Your control over your data

Because everything lives in a folder on your device, you are always in full control. You can view, move, back up, or permanently delete your notes and recordings at any time using Flaunt or your device's file manager. Deleting the app or its storage folder removes your content from that location.

## Changes to this policy

If this policy changes, the updated version will be provided with the app and the "Effective date" above will be revised. Because Flaunt collects no data, any changes will simply reflect updates to the app's functionality.

